UML:TaggedValue.value:
People will be able to visit uStore even without registering. However, the operations they would be able to perform on the site would be limited. The unregistered users would be able to: 1. Search for AAL services. However, since uStore would not recognize the user, the search would not be customized to the user. 2. Order free AAL services 3. Read feedback about AAL services
The unregistered users would not be able to order non-free AAL services, sign agreements, provide feedback.
Search, explore and download free AAL services

UML:Class.name: 7. Informal caregiver helps AP to find required AAL service

UML:TaggedValue.value: Informal caregiver (for example relative of AP) registers uStore and defines his role and connection to AP. uStore asks for permission from AP to add this person as his caregiver and to allow him to see/use part of his personal information. After confirmation, the caregiver can login to uStore and search based on platform and specific needs of the AP. Finally caregiver finds some appropriate service for AP and offers it to AP through uStore. AP can select to order it or to ignore the offer.

UML:TaggedValue.value:
A company, that specializes in deployment of AAL services, decides to create a new service - "fall detection and monitoring".
1. Hardware - a fall detection devices 2. 24/7 monitoring center - a legacy service with Web Services API 3. A software to be installed at home of the assisted person, for controlling the bracelet and communication with the 24/7 monitoring service 4.The installation service of the devices, provided by the deploying company itself
The deploying company constructs these new service from 1) Fall detection devices sold by a devices company 2) monitoring service proposed a monitoring center company 3) A software written for the deploying company by a software developer 4) the installation service of the deploying company itself. The software written for the "fall detection and monitoring" service, listens to the signals from the fall detection devices, processes the received information and once it decides that the fall is detected, it informs the 24/7 monitoring center via its Web Service API. Here the deploying company combined hardware and a legacy service, added to it specially developed software and its own installation service, and the result of this syndication is a new, more complex solution.
